The Beijing Platform for Action and the final outcome document of the United Nations General Assembly Special Session on Beijing + 5, last June, are along the same lines.
The Finnish Presidency' s report on woman and decision-making set out clear indicator for evaluating the progress made.
I also want to salute the Commission' s initiative - I think my information is correct, Mrs Diamantopoulou - in taking a decision to have parity between men and woman within it committee and group of experts.
We must all commit ourselves to following and developing this encouraging initiative.
The French Presidency would like to make progress in this matter and hope to approach it partner with proposal for quantified target for giving woman access to decision-making in all areas, the political arena, which I have already mentioned, but also economic and social sectors.
