If we want third country to accept commitments, the European Community must be the most zealous in ensuring that it own rule are being complied with, because if a country ha the opportunity to place product in the Community by mean of smuggling, why is it going to bother to negotiate with u for any sort of concessions?
I therefore welcome the fact that we have reached an agreement on this subject.
I think that the modification are very positive, but I would like to take this opportunity to ask the Commission for greater vigilance and for stricter measure on fraud in Community customs.
Mr President, Commissioner, lady and gentlemen, although it is true that the text is flawed, a the Chairman of the Committee on Legal Affairs and the Internal Market and the rapporteur have already underlined, I would still venture to suggest that this legislative resolution is an example of transparent, simplified and efficient Community legislation.
