In broader terms, the Community Customs Code is one of the most important legal instrument for establishing the amount of outstanding duty and to establish to whom these are due.
The code form the legal basis for levying these duty and, a such, one of the key instrument for protecting the financial interest of the Community and for ensuring the smooth running of the Community policy in different areas.
