Mr President, that I personally am saddened and angered by the sinking and on behalf of it victim doe without saying, although I suppose that we shall never completely do away with accident at sea and shipwrecks. But what really irritates and anger me are shortcomings, imperfections, derogation and the problem which this sinking ha brought to light and that is why we need to debate them;
