Mr President, lady and gentlemen, there are two people here today who deserve special congratulations, one being Anna Lancker, for her outstanding report, and the other being Anna Diamantopoulou, for her outstanding submission.
It is an ambitious agenda, and I still have a clear recollection of the painfully slow progress that wa made during the last legislative period in the sphere of social protection.
