Mr President, Commissioner, Minister, lady and gentlemen, the citizen of the European Union expect more than just vague commitment that are then forgotten and which are rarely converted into binding instrument or decision that bring about a real improvement in the quality of their life and of their work. In order to dispel any lack of confidence, this social agenda must enable objective and policy that have been postponed for year to be put into practice.
